BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Little Shop of Horrors
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270403T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270403T223000
DTSTAMP:20260707T000730Z
UID:occ-1634@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Menken and Ashman's doo-wop horror comedy: a skid row florist\
 , a bloodthirsty plant\, and a Faustian bargain.\n\nThe 1982 horror-comedy
  musical from Alan Menken and Howard Ashman\, the songwriting team that la
 ter gave Disney The Little Mermaid. Meek flower-shop clerk Seymour discove
 rs a strange plant that turns his fortunes around\, but Audrey II has a ta
 ste for blood and an appetite that keeps growing. The score runs on early-
 '60s rock and roll\, doo-wop\, and Motown\, with a girl-group trio of stre
 et urchins as Greek chorus. Presented by Stage Door Theatre.
GEO:33.9447222;-84.3319444
LAST-MODIFIED:20260706T063411Z
LOCATION:Stage Door Theatre\, 5339 Chamblee Dunwoody Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36385/performance/11825819/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
